{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"25":{"eng-name":"Chapters on Hajj Rituals","ara-name":"كتاب المناسك"}},"section_detail":{"25":{"hadithnumber_first":2882,"hadithnumber_last":3119,"arabicnumber_first":2882,"arabicnumber_last":3119}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":2974,"arabicnumber":2974,"text":"It was narrated from Ibn ‘Umar that he came (to Makkah) to perform Hajj and ‘Umrah together (Qiran). He circumambulated the House seven times, and performed Sa’y between Safa and Marwah, then he said:“This is what the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) did.”","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Daif"}],"reference":{"book":25,"hadith":93},"chapter":{"id":39,"ara-name":"باب طَوَافِ الْقَارِنِ","eng-name":"Tawaf for one performing Qiran","isFirstHadith":false}}]}